id: pm-7tug
title: Extract shared temporary-directory lifecycle helpers for tests
description: "Duplicate audit 2026-05-22: test files locally repeat mkdtemp(path.join(os.tmpdir(), prefix)), callback execution, and rm(..., { recursive: true, force: true }) cleanup. Representative helpers are tests/unit/fs-utils.spec.ts:14 withTempDir, tests/unit/search-cache.spec.ts:15 withTempDir, tests/unit/config-command.spec.ts:20 withTempRoot, tests/unit/settings-store.spec.ts:12 withTempRoot, tests/unit/telemetry-runtime.spec.ts:34 withTempGlobalRoot, and tests/unit/telemetry-consent.spec.ts:9 withTempGlobalRoot. This is distinct from pm-ibyi legacy settings fixtures and pm-eltf item factories."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 3
tags[4]: code-quality,dedup,fixtures,tests
created_at: "2026-05-22T19:17:40.595Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-23T19:58:53.156Z"
author: codex-duplicate-audit
acceptance_criteria: Generic withTempDir and specialized withTempGlobalRoot/withTempRoot helpers live under tests/helpers; affected tests consume them instead of local lifecycle copies; cleanup remains force-recursive and safe; targeted tests and pnpm build pass.
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: Shared temp root helpers extracted and merged in PR #52.
expected_result: Tests keep isolated PM_PATH and PM_GLOBAL_PATH behavior while duplicate temp-directory setup is reduced.
actual_result: "tests/helpers/temp.ts centralizes temp roots; Gemini feedback removed implicit PM_GLOBAL_PATH mutation; focused tests, full release gate, manual dogfood, GitHub checks, and AI review follow-up passed."
